    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-24T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-24T21:00:00-05:00" n="798"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/135: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-25T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1919—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Legation’s November 24, 4 p.m. Russian Legation has protested to the Chinese
                    Government regarding cancellation of Russian agreements with China and Mongolia
                    of 1912, 1913 and 1915<note n="5" xml:id="d798fn5">MacMurray, <hi rend="italic"
                            >Treaties</hi> vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 992, 1066, and
                        1239, respectively.</note> reserving all Russian rights under said
                    agreement[s].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
